5|$|The first <b>Jackie</b> <b>Robinson</b> Day was on April 15, 2004. That {{day was a}} {{start to}} an annual {{tradition}} throughout Major League Baseball and an inspirational reminder about what happened on that day exactly fifty-seven years earlier when <b>Jackie</b> <b>Robinson</b> became a Major League Baseball player. The day {{would be the first}} official league-wide <b>Jackie</b> <b>Robinson</b> Day, having festivities taking place at all 23 ballparks where Major League games were scheduled to be played. Baseball Commissioner Bud Selig made the announcement with Sharon Robinson (daughter of Rachel and <b>Jackie</b> <b>Robinson).</b>|$|E
